Description: This elaborate Bollywood epic dramatizes one man's transformation from a vengeful and cunning warrior into a legendary leader and teacher of Buddhism.

Title: Motu Patlu: King of Kings
Cast: Saurav Chakrabarty, Vinay Pathak
Description: Motu and Patlu want to help a circus lion get back to the jungle. On the way, the three become caught up in an exciting adventure in the forest.

Title: Mubarakan
Cast: Anil Kapoor, Arjun Kapoor, Ileana D'Cruz, Athiya Shetty, Neha Sharma, Vineet Kumar Singh, Pavan Malhotra, Ratna Pathak Shah, Karan Kundra, Anil Mange, Rahul Dev, Sanjay Kapoor
Description: Chaos ensues after two orphaned twin brothers raised apart team up with their eccentric, unmarried uncle to find a solution to their romantic woes.

Title: Krish Trish and Baltiboy: Face Your Fears
Cast: Tarun Ratnani, Smita Malhotra, Deepak Chachra
Description: In three tales about fear, a baby elephant gets captured by a circus, two boys enter a haunted house and a parrot faces his fear of flying.

Title: Poster Boys
Cast: Sunny Deol, Bobby Deol, Shreyas Talpade, Sonali Kulkarni, Tripti Dimri, Samiksha Bhatnagar, Lovely Singh, Purnima Varma
Description: Three men are stunned to find their faces on a poster promoting vasectomies, and must prove to their upset loved ones that they're innocent victims.

Title: Fandry
Cast: Somnath Awghade, Suraj Pawar, Chhaya Kadam, Kishore Kadam, Rajeshwari Kharat, Bhushan Manjule, Nagraj Manjule, Sohail Shaikh, Sanjay Chaudhri, Vikas Pandurang Patil
Description: Spunky, lower-caste lad Jabya falls for lovely, upper-caste Shalu. But his family's derided social position proves a stubborn stumbling block to love.

Title: Hum Saath-Saath Hain
Cast: Salman Khan, Karisma Kapoor, Saif Ali Khan, Tabu, Sonali Bendre, Mohnish Bahl, Mahesh Thakur, Neelam, Alok Nath, Satish Shah
Description: A scheming matriarch plots to cut off her disabled stepson and his wife from the family fortune, creating a division within the clan.

Title: Iqbal
Cast: Shreyas Talpade, Naseeruddin Shah, Girish Karnad, Shweta Prasad, Yatin Karyekar, Prateeksha Lonkar, Dilip Salgaonkar, Jyoti Joshi, Aadarsh Balakrishna, Gururaj Manepalli
Description: A boy with a hearing and speech impairment – and extraordinary athletic ability – chases his lifelong dream of playing cricket for India.

Title: Th Eena Meena Deeka Chase Comedy Show
Cast: Sanjay Keni, Priya Raina
Description: A hungry fox and three resourceful, surprisingly formidable birds turn the animal kingdom on its head in this lively animated series.

Title: Pad Man
Cast: Akshay Kumar, Sonam Kapoor, Radhika Apte, Jyoti Subhash, Urmila Mahanta, Suneel Sinha, Sanjay Singh, Rakesh Chaturvedi Om
Description: Despite public humiliation and resistance, an entrepreneur markets a hygienic, low-cost sanitary pad that even India's poorest women can afford.

Title: Siddhant

Description: A principled mathematics teacher is shocked to discover that his grandson used unethical means to achieve academic success.

Title: Zokkomon
Cast: Darsheel Safary, Anupam Kher, Manjari Fadnis, Tinnu Anand, Sheeba Chaddha, S.M. Zaheer, Aayam Mehta, Gargi Datar, Jai Vyas
Description: When his cruel uncle abandons him, a young orphan learns to access the untapped superpowers that have been waiting within him all along.

Title: Super Bheem Bana Vajraveer
Cast: Sonal Kaushal, Rupa Bhimani, Julie Tejwani, Sabina Malik, Jigna Bharadhwaj, Rajesh Kawa
Description: Hoping to find a magical root, a monster has captured farmers in the land of Vyom. It’s up to Bheem and the gang to foil his plan and save the kingdom!

Title: Chhota Bheem Kungfu Dhamaka
Cast: Sonal Kaushal, Rupa Bhimani, Jigna Bharadhwaj, Sabina Malik, Julie Tejwani, Rajesh Kava, Vaibhav Thakkar, Samriddhi Shuklaa, Aditya Raj Sharma, Vinod Kulkarni
Description: Chhota Bheem is in China for a martial arts competition but his real challenge: to save the emperor’s daughter from being kidnapped by the villain Zuhu!

Title: Together For Eternity
Cast: Salman Khan, Karisma Kapoor, Saif Ali Khan, Tabu, Sonali Bendre, Mohnish Bahl, Reema Lagoo, Mahesh Thakur, Neelam, Alok Nath
Description: A scheming matriarch plots to cut off her disabled stepson and his wife from the family fortune, creating a division within the clan.

Title: A truthful Mother
Cast: Revathi, Roger Narayanan, Sneha Ravishankar, Vidya Shankar, SR Leela
Description: Facing a drought, a hungry tiger and a noble cow have an extraordinary encounter in this fable based on a children’s book and a Kannada folk song.

Title: Chhota Bheem and the Curse of Damyaan
Cast: Kaustav Ghosh, Jigna Bhardwaj, Chutki, Rajesh Kava, Mausam, Guru Shambu, Arun Shekar, Julie Tejwani, Anamaya Verma

Title: Taare Zameen Par
Cast: Aamir Khan, Darsheel Safary, Tanay Chheda, Tisca Chopra, Vipin Sharma, Girija Oak, M.K. Raina
Description: When daydreamer Ishaan is sent to boarding school, an unconventional art teacher tries to help the imaginative student discover his true identity.

Title: Chhota Bheem And The Broken Amulet
Cast: Vatsal Dubey, Julie Tejwani, Rupa Bhimani, Jigna Bhardwaj, Rajesh Kava, Mousam, Swapnil
Description: When a stranger tries to steal an amulet from the palace, Bheem learns the sad story behind the ornament and heads to Africa to defeat the real villain.

Title: Chhota Bheem aur Krishna
Cast: Vatsal Dubey, Julie Tejwani, Rupa Bhimani, Jigna Bhardwaj, Rajesh Kava, Arun Shekher, Sanchit Wartak
Description: Centuries after the end of a conqueror's rule, he is mysteriously back from the dead. It’s up to Bheem to save Dholakpur from being taken over!
